UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Lander GONZALEZ-LOPEZ, Defendant-Appellant. No. 09-20092

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 15, 2009. James Lee Turner, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Andrew J. Williams, Kingwood, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Before KING, JOLLY, and SOUTHWICK, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Lander Gonzalez-Lopez has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Gonzalez-Lopez has filed a response. Our independent review of the record, counsel’s brief, and Gonzalez-Lopez’s response discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
